<div class="js-curloc-error-modal curloc-error-modal hidden">
<div class="modal_head">
<h2>Oops, we can't find your location</h2>
</div>
<div class="modal_body">
<div class="curloc-permission-denied hidden">
<p>
First, try refreshing the page and clicking Current Location again. Make sure you click <b>Allow</b> or <b>Grant Permissions</b> if your browser asks for your location. If your browser doesn't ask you, try these steps:
</p>
<div class="chrome hidden">
<ol class="modal_section u-bg-color">
<li>At the top of your Chrome window, near the web address, click <b>the green lock labeled Secure</b>.</li>
<li>In the window that pops up, make sure <b>Location</b> is set to <b>Ask</b> or <b>Allow</b>.</li>
<li>You're good to go! Reload this Yelp page and try your search again.</li>
</ol>
<p>
If you're still having trouble, check out <a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/142065?co=GENIE.Platform%3DDesktop&hl=en&oco=0" target="_blank">Google's support page</a>.
You can also search near a city, place, or address instead.
</p>
</div>
<div class="opera hidden">
<ol class="modal_section u-bg-color">
<li>At the top of your Opera window, near the web address, you should see a <b>gray location pin</b>. Click it.</li>
<li>In the window that pops up, click <b>Clear This Setting</b></li>
<li>You're good to go! Reload this Yelp page and try your search again.</li>
</ol>
<p>
If you're still having trouble, check out <a target="_blank">Opera's support page</a>.
You can also search near a city, place, or address instead.
</p>
</div>
<div class="safari hidden">
<ol class="modal_section u-bg-color">
<li>Click <b>Safari</b> in the Menu Bar at the top of the screen, then <b>Preferences</b>.</li>
<li>Click the <b>Privacy</b> tab.</li>
<li>Under <b>Website use of location services</b>, click <b>Prompt for each website once each day</b> or <b>Prompt for each website one time only</b>.</li>
<li>MacOS may now prompt you to enable Location Services. If it does, follow its instructions to enable Location Services for Safari.</li>
<li>Close the Privacy menu and refresh the page. Try using Current Location search again. If it works, great! If not, read on for more instructions.</li>
<li>Back in the <b>Privacy</b> dialog, Click <b>Manage Website Data...</b> and type <b>yelp.com</b> into the search bar.</li>
<li>Click the <b>yelp.com</b> entry and click Remove.</li>
<li>You're good to go! Close the Settings tab, reload this Yelp page, and try your search again.</li>
</ol>
<p>
If you're still having trouble, check out <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT204690" target="_blank">Safari's support page</a>.
You can also search near a city, place, or address instead.
</p>
</div>
<div class="firefox hidden">
<ol class="modal_section u-bg-color">
<li>At the top of your Firefox window, to the left of the web address, you should see a <b>green lock</b>. Click it.</li>
<li>In the window that pops up, you should see <b>Blocked</b> or <b>Blocked Temporarily</b> next to <b>Access Your Location</b>. Click the <b>x</b> next to this line.</li>
<li>You're good to go! Refresh this Yelp page and try your search again.</li>
</ol>
<p>
If you're still having trouble, check out <a href="https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/geolocation/" target="_blank">Firefox's support page</a>.
You can also search near a city, place, or address instead.
</p>
</div>
<div class="ie hidden">
<ol class="modal_section u-bg-color">
<li>Click the <b>gear</b> in the upper-right hand corner of the window, then <b>Internet options</b>.</li>
<li>Click the <b>Privacy</b> tab in the new window that just appeared.</li>
<li>Uncheck the box labeled <b>Never allow websites to request your physical location</b> if it's already checked.</li>
<li>Click the button labeled <b>Clear Sites</b>.</li>
<li>You're good to go! Click <b>OK</b>, then refresh this Yelp page and try your search again.</li>
</ol>
<p>
You can also search near a city, place, or address instead.
</p>
</div>
<div class="edge hidden">
<ol class="modal_section u-bg-color">
<li>At the top-right hand corner of the window, click the <b>button with three dots on it</b>, then <b>Settings</b>.</li>
<li>Click <b>Choose what to clear</b> underneath <b>Clear browsing data</b>.</li>
<li>Click <b>Show more</b>, then make sure only the box labeled <b>Location permissions</b> is checked.</li>
<li>Click <b>Clear</b>.</li>
<li>You're good to go! Refresh this Yelp page and try your search again.</li>
</ol>
<p>
You can also search near a city, place, or address instead.
</p>

<div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
<meta itemprop="author" content="Miguel H.">
<div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
<meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="4.0">
</div>
<meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2017-03-24">
<p itemprop="description">I was visiting a friend in Daly City and we decided to have our last meal here. We came on a Sunday for brunch which was definitely a mistake since going to brunch on a Sunday in an upscale San Francisco neighborhood seems to be an idea that a ton of people have. We ended up waiting outside for about an hour and a half until our names were finally called.

The food was pretty good. I ordered 3 eggs Benedict with fontina cheese and bacon with a side of their home fries. It was really tasty but a little overpriced for what it was in my opinion (I paid about $25). I also had a sip of my friend&#39;s mocha (which they serve in bowls rather than cups oddly enough), and it was delicious.

We sat in a semi-open area in the back which had a very chill vibe perfect for brunch. It got a bit crowded but there were a ton of people trying to eat and the restaurant was doing their best to seat everyone. The service was great. The waitress we had was super friendly and more than willing to help me make a good choice on the menu. Something cool about this place is that they actually recommend not tipping their employees. They list a bunch of benefits that their employees enjoy on their menu. Its always great to support a business that truly takes care of their workers.

I had a good time here and the food was yummy, but if I ever come back I will definitely avoid the brunch rush because it wasn&#39;t really worth the hour and a half wait.<p>
</div>

And yes, it&#39;s nice that you present all the food at once for the entire table, but its upsetting to know that other tables will receive their food first after being seated after us. <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
<meta itemprop="author" content="Scott K.">
<div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
<meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="4.0">
</div>
<meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2017-12-02">
<p itemprop="description">Definitely a cute place if you&#39;re looking for a cute picturesque photo spot. Back garden area is pretty with all the lights and grapes of different colors hanging down contrasting from the green vines.

Food however, is pretty standard as to most brunch places. The selection for benedicts here is a bit larger as they have many different options, but I was surprised the classic benedict was not on the menu as I tend to like more meat.

The food took a very long time to come out, probably around 30 to 40 minutes honestly. Really not sure what took so long. Professional restaurants should have food out around the 15 minute mark.

I decided to order the omelet and had no problems generally, however adding more chicken sausage would have been a major plus. After the meal, I was only about 60% full, so that was a bit disappointing.

If you want to visit the world&#39;s smallest restroom, be sure to hit this place up. Difficult to even turn around without hitting the sink.

Overall, a solid brunch spot.<p>
</div>

<div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
<meta itemprop="author" content="Peter C.">
<div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
<meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="4.0">
</div>
<meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2016-02-06">
<p itemprop="description">Zazie is a great place to come for breakfast and brunch. I found this place on my yelp app and was not disappointed. When I arrived about mid morning, there was already a long wait list. The quoted wait time to sit inside was longer than the patio. I opted for the patio because I was simply hungry and didn&#39;t want to wait longer. The outdoor seating has patio heaters which was a huge plus. Seating at Zazie is a little tight and limited. If you are coming with a large group this place might not be for you.

I ordered the poached egg, Monaco. The Monaco comes with prosciutto and roasted tomatoes provencales (see my pic). This was served on top of an English muffin with their house sauce and pan fried potatoes. You have an option to order this with one or two eggs. I got mine with two eggs.

All quoted items on the menu includes tips. Zazie is a &#34;tip free&#34; restaurant, which is cool for those who don&#39;t like to tip. I still left one because I felt the service was phenomenal. My waiter kept my coffee filled and was on point with his service, which is one of the reasons why I would return.<p>
</div>

My friend and I sat outside and the ambience was really nice. <p itemprop="description">Went to Zazie this morning with my parents for brunch. We arrived at 8:30 and waited in line for 20 minutes to add our names to the waitlist. We were seated right after 9am when they open.

I always love the patio space with their outdoor tables and heat lamps. It was a cozy fall vibe. We ordered coffee cake, the Divorcee (eggs Benedict with bacon and cheese) and the omelet special with tomatoes and chicken sausage. The food is really where things were bad. The omelet was cold in the middle and SO heavy on the garlic. The eggs Benedict was warm but I wouldn&#39;t call it hot. It had a tiny amount of avocado and for $20 it&#39;s ridiculous even for SF. Service was fine but I really can&#39;t get over the logistics and the wait for barely mediocre food.<p>

<div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
<meta itemprop="author" content="Venus L.">
<div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
<meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="4.0">
</div>
<meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2016-04-05">
<p itemprop="description">My boyfriend wanted to one up me and take me to Zazie&#39;s for brunch. I guess I&#39;ll have to give it to him this time. Zazie&#39;s was good.

Located on Cole St., there&#39;s no doubt that Zazie&#39;s was going to be busy especially on a Sunday afternoon. Parking was also hell so I should mention that. My boyfriend and I circled a few residential blocks before finally parking 3 blocks away. But the weather was nice so the walk wasn&#39;t too bad.

Zazie&#39;s has a wait list posted on the window near the door so be aware of that. Don&#39;t just stand around with the people outside waiting. There are four 2-seater tables outside that are FIRST COME, FIRST SERVE. So even if you&#39;re number 20 on the list and there are other couples before you, if you grab a table out from then you&#39;re good. Seems like a dick move really, but that&#39;s what my boyfriend and I did. And it was a good thing, too, because the manager ended up calling my boyfriend&#39;s name for a table right when we were pretty much done eating so if we didn&#39;t swoop in then we would&#39;ve had to wait a good 40-50 mins just for a table.

Service here was okay. The waiter we had wasn&#39;t overly friendly but he worked efficiently and the bus boy was nice enough to clear the table when we first sat down even though he already had a lot of plates in his hands. There&#39;s no tipping involved here because they all get paid a living wage which I&#39;ve never heard of before but sounds pretty darn awesome!

My boyfriend ordered their miracle pancakes (which changes flavors so I&#39;m not quite sure what to tell you) but it had lemon curd and strawberries on top and it was good. Their sides are a tad expensive for one egg and sausages. I got their Tahiti French toast with caramelized bananas and walnuts and it was delicious but ended up being too sweet towards the end. I think if we were to come back we&#39;ll try their savory dishes instead.

Overall, Zazie&#39;s in. Boyfriend 1, girlfriend 0.<p>
</div>

<meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-01-22">
<p itemprop="description">Small cute space. Good vibe and friendly workers.
The food is average. The flavor is there but I had a few burnt potatoes in my home fries, and they didn&#39;t actually toast my toast, while burning the edges of my friends toast.
I went mid morning on a Monday and was lucky to find a place to seat a group of 5. Most of the tables are set up for two.
The bathroom is extremely small and awkward, as the door does not close shut, it is just a barn style door and you can hear the workers talking right outside.
I ordered the Greece scramble and was pleased with the flavor as well as the amount of spinach onion and feta in the eggs.
It&#39;s a cute little place with good food, I would suggest it if you are near by looking for brunch but it doesn&#39;t hit the &#34;must have&#34; list for me.<p>

<h3 class="alternate u-line-break">How long is the wait usually for brunch on a Saturday?</h3>
</div>
</div>

<div class="u-space-t1">
<div class="arrange arrange--12">
<div class="arrange_unit">
<div class="photo-box pb-30s" data-hovercard-id="gqkk9zsTrBQFyoJ0J3df8Q">
<a href="/user_details?userid=MxhUqyI7LbQ28SFTbnv6CA" class="js-analytics-click" data-analytics-label="user-photo">
<img alt="Roojuta L." class="photo-box-img" height="30" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/wgr5v5lIU-sT_khTyHmugQ/30s.jpg" srcset="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/wgr5v5lIU-sT_khTyHmugQ/60s.jpg 2.00x,https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/wgr5v5lIU-sT_khTyHmugQ/90s.jpg 3.00x,https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/wgr5v5lIU-sT_khTyHmugQ/ss.jpg 1.33x" width="30">

</a>

</div>



</div>
<div class="arrange_unit arrange_unit--fill">
<div class="js-answer-expander">
<p class="js-content-expanded u-hidden u-line-break u-break-word u-space-b1">We waiting for ~30 minutes on Saturday. It is pretty busy and they do not take reservations! I would expect 30-60 minutes wait. But there are seats ( 4 small tables ) outside which has no wait time, if is first come first serve. <a href="javascript:;" class="js-read-less">Read less</a>
</p>
<p class="js-content-truncated u-line-break u-break-word u-space-b1">We waiting for ~30 minutes on Saturday. It is pretty busy and they do not take reservations! I would expect 30-60 minutes wait. But there are seats ( 4 small tables ) outside which has no wait time, if is first come first serve. </p>

<div class="review-wrapper">
<div class="review-content">
<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-4 rating-large" title="4.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="4.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
3/24/2017
</span>

</div>

<ul class="review-tags">
<li class="review-tags_item">

<span >
<span aria-hidden="true" style="fill: #0077bc; width: 18px; height: 18px;" class="icon icon--18-check-in icon--size-18 u-space-r-half">
<svg role="img" class="icon_svg">
<use xlink:href="#18x18_check_in" />
</svg>
</span>1 check-in
</span>
</li>

</ul>


<p lang="en">I was visiting a friend in Daly City and we decided to have our last meal here. We came on a Sunday for brunch which was definitely a mistake since going to brunch on a Sunday in an upscale San Francisco neighborhood seems to be an idea that a ton of people have. We ended up waiting outside for about an hour and a half until our names were finally called. <br><br>The food was pretty good. I ordered 3 eggs Benedict with fontina cheese and bacon with a side of their home fries. It was really tasty but a little overpriced for what it was in my opinion (I paid about $25). I also had a sip of my friend&#39;s mocha (which they serve in bowls rather than cups oddly enough), and it was delicious. <br><br>We sat in a semi-open area in the back which had a very chill vibe perfect for brunch. It got a bit crowded but there were a ton of people trying to eat and the restaurant was doing their best to seat everyone. The service was great. The waitress we had was super friendly and more than willing to help me make a good choice on the menu. Something cool about this place is that they actually recommend not tipping their employees. They list a bunch of benefits that their employees enjoy on their menu. Its always great to support a business that truly takes care of their workers. <br><br>I had a good time here and the food was yummy, but if I ever come back I will definitely avoid the brunch rush because it wasn&#39;t really worth the hour and a half wait.</p>

<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-3 rating-large" title="3.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="3.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
5/7/2018
</span>

</div>

<p lang="en">Cute little brunch place in the Cole Valley.  I highly recommend coming here when they first open, otherwise, you&#39;ll be waiting for a loooong time for a table and food.  I like the no-tip concept and the portions are decent for the price you pay.  And yes, it&#39;s nice that you present all the food at once for the entire table, but its upsetting to know that other tables will receive their food first after being seated after us.  After being seated and our orders were promptly taken, it took about 30-45 minutes for our courses to show up.  It&#39;ll be a while until I return....if I ever return.</p>
</div>

<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-5 rating-large" title="5.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="5.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
9/19/2017
</span>

</div>

<p lang="en">Breakfast lovers; do yourself a favor.  Walk on over to this cozy nook and order a piece of breakfast heaven.  Providing an amazing menu with amazing bites is one thing, but when you incorporate a bar with specialty drinks?  Fun days at its finest.  Not just for Sundays.  Seriously.</p>

<div class="review-wrapper">
<div class="review-content">
<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-4 rating-large" title="4.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="4.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
12/2/2017
</span>

</div>

<ul class="review-tags">
<li class="review-tags_item">

<span >
<span aria-hidden="true" style="fill: #0077bc; width: 18px; height: 18px;" class="icon icon--18-check-in icon--size-18 u-space-r-half">
<svg role="img" class="icon_svg">
<use xlink:href="#18x18_check_in" />
</svg>
</span>1 check-in
</span>
</li>

</ul>


<p lang="en">Definitely a cute place if you&#39;re looking for a cute picturesque photo spot. Back garden area is pretty with all the lights and grapes of different colors hanging down contrasting from the green vines. <br><br>Food however, is pretty standard as to most brunch places. The selection for benedicts here is a bit larger as they have many different options, but I was surprised the classic benedict was not on the menu as I tend to like more meat. <br><br>The food took a very long time to come out, probably around 30 to 40 minutes honestly. Really not sure what took so long. Professional restaurants should have food out around the 15 minute mark. <br><br>I decided to order the omelet and had no problems generally, however adding more chicken sausage would have been a major plus. After the meal, I was only about 60% full, so that was a bit disappointing. <br><br>If you want to visit the world&#39;s smallest restroom, be sure to hit this place up. Difficult to even turn around without hitting the sink. <br><br>Overall, a solid brunch spot.</p>
</div>

<div class="review-wrapper">
<div class="review-content">
<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-4 rating-large" title="4.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="4.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
2/6/2016
</span>

</div>

<p lang="en">Zazie is a great place to come for breakfast and brunch.  I found this place on my yelp app and was not disappointed.  When I arrived about mid morning, there was already a long wait list.  The quoted wait time to sit inside was longer than the patio.  I opted for the patio because I was simply hungry and didn&#39;t want to wait longer.  The outdoor seating has patio heaters which was a  huge plus.  Seating at Zazie is a little tight and limited.  If you are coming with a large group this place might not be for you.<br><br>I ordered the poached egg, Monaco.  The Monaco comes with prosciutto and roasted tomatoes provencales (see my pic).  This was served on top of an English muffin with their house sauce and pan fried potatoes.  You have an option to order this with one or two eggs.  I got mine with two eggs.<br><br>All quoted items on the menu includes tips.  Zazie is a &#34;tip free&#34; restaurant, which is cool for those who don&#39;t like to tip.  I still left one because I felt the service was phenomenal.  My waiter kept my coffee filled and was on point with his service, which is one of the reasons why I would return.</p>

<div class="review-content">
<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-3 rating-large" title="3.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="3.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
2/2/2016
</span>

</div>

<p lang="en">I was really excited to try this French brunch place and to see if it was anything like the French brunch place La Note back at Berkeley. The servers here were all very friendly, and we got seated in the cute outdoor patio.<br><br>I ordered a quite an expensive buttermilk pancake, so I was expecting it to be really good. It was nice and crispy on the outside and soft on the inside. Honestly, it was not anything special and I was quite disappointed. This place is a &#34;no tip&#34; restaurant, but you can definitely see that the prices of the food are raised because of this. My friend and I sat outside and the ambience was really nice. Overall, it was a nice ambience and the food was decent but it was definitely not worth the high prices, so I don&#39;t think I will be coming back.</p>

<div class="review-wrapper">
<div class="review-content">
<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-2 rating-large" title="2.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="2.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
11/5/2017
</span>

</div>

<p lang="en">Went to Zazie this morning with my parents for brunch. We arrived at 8:30 and waited in line for 20 minutes to add our names to the waitlist. We were seated right after 9am when they open.<br><br>I always love the patio space with their outdoor tables and heat lamps. It was a cozy fall vibe. We ordered coffee cake, the Divorcee (eggs Benedict with bacon and cheese) and the omelet special with tomatoes and chicken sausage. The food is really where things were bad. The omelet was cold in the middle and SO heavy on the garlic. The eggs Benedict was warm but I wouldn&#39;t call it hot. It had a tiny amount of avocado and for $20 it&#39;s ridiculous even for SF. Service was fine but I really can&#39;t get over the logistics and the wait for barely mediocre food.</p>
</div>

<div class="review-wrapper">
<div class="review-content">
<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-4 rating-large" title="4.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="4.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
4/5/2016
</span>

</div>

<ul class="review-tags">
<li class="review-tags_item">

<span >
<span aria-hidden="true" style="fill: #0077bc; width: 18px; height: 18px;" class="icon icon--18-check-in icon--size-18 u-space-r-half">
<svg role="img" class="icon_svg">
<use xlink:href="#18x18_check_in" />
</svg>
</span>1 check-in
</span>
</li>

</ul>


<p lang="en">My boyfriend wanted to one up me and take me to Zazie&#39;s for brunch. I guess I&#39;ll have to give it to him this time. Zazie&#39;s was good. <br><br>Located on Cole St., there&#39;s no doubt that Zazie&#39;s was going to be busy especially on a Sunday afternoon. Parking was also hell so I should mention that. My boyfriend and I circled a few residential blocks before finally parking 3 blocks away. But the weather was nice so the walk wasn&#39;t too bad. <br><br>Zazie&#39;s has a wait list posted on the window near the door so be aware of that. Don&#39;t just stand around with the people outside waiting. There are four 2-seater tables outside that are FIRST COME, FIRST SERVE. So even if you&#39;re number 20 on the list and there are other couples before you, if you grab a table out from then you&#39;re good. Seems like a dick move really, but that&#39;s what my boyfriend and I did. And it was a good thing, too, because the manager ended up calling my boyfriend&#39;s name for a table right when we were pretty much done eating so if we didn&#39;t swoop in then we would&#39;ve had to wait a good 40-50 mins just for a table. <br><br>Service here was okay. The waiter we had wasn&#39;t overly friendly but he worked efficiently and the bus boy was nice enough to clear the table when we first sat down even though he already had a lot of plates in his hands. There&#39;s no tipping involved here because they all get paid a living wage which I&#39;ve never heard of before but sounds pretty darn awesome!<br><br>My boyfriend ordered their miracle pancakes (which changes flavors so I&#39;m not quite sure what to tell you) but it had lemon curd and strawberries on top and it was good. Their sides are a tad expensive for one egg and sausages. I got their Tahiti French toast with caramelized bananas and walnuts and it was delicious but ended up being too sweet towards the end. I think if we were to come back we&#39;ll try their savory dishes instead. <br><br>Overall, Zazie&#39;s in. Boyfriend 1, girlfriend 0.</p>

<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-1 rating-large" title="1.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="1.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
5/2/2018
</span>

</div>

<p lang="en">Came here on a weekday and was seated right away. However, after 15 minutes of waiting, no one came to our table. While there&#39;s no tipping, the prices were laughable. $21 for 3 plain buttermilk pancakes?!? There&#39;s no excuse for $21 pancakes unless they were perhaps topped with barrel-aged maple syrup and foie gras. I&#39;d also say the poor service is what you get when you don&#39;t have to work for tips. By the way, after 15 minutes of waiting, we walked out. This is absolutely the SF version of Nello (if Nello was a breakfast place).</p>
</div>

<div class="review-wrapper">
<div class="review-content">
<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-4 rating-large" title="4.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="4.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
10/2/2017
</span>

</div>

<ul class="review-tags">
<li class="review-tags_item">

<span >
<span aria-hidden="true" style="fill: #0077bc; width: 18px; height: 18px;" class="icon icon--18-check-in icon--size-18 u-space-r-half">
<svg role="img" class="icon_svg">
<use xlink:href="#18x18_check_in" />
</svg>
</span>1 check-in
</span>
</li>

</ul>


<p lang="en">Finally brunched at Zazie! It was a random weekday so I didn&#39;t expect there to be a full house! We still managed to get a cute 2 person som table on the patio. The patio is adorable and I highly recommend it if dining for brunch or dinner on a nice night.<br><br>I had the BLT on the lunch menu because it was a very hot day, the breakfast items although delicious sounding seemed on the heavier side. <br><br>The BLT was definitively delicious, bacon was crispy and the toppings blended together nicely with the delicious focaccia. I do think it&#39;s a tad on the pricy side $17 with it just coming with a salad - but then again it&#39;s Zazie and it&#39;s developed that sort of a following! <br><br>I&#39;d love to go back and try a few other things!</p>
</div>

<div class="review-content">
<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-5 rating-large" title="5.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="5.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
2/5/2018
</span>

</div>

<p lang="en">Sat us right away on a Monday at about 11:30. Weird first impression when one of their servers snapped at us to wait by the front when we&#39;d never been there before and had no idea where we were supposed to wait to be greeted and seated (there was no sign and no one standing there.) But we witnessed the same server treat another group poorly too - we&#39;ll give him the benefit of the doubt and say he was having a bad day, because this place was great. Really full menu, excellent cappuccino, and our food came out pretty fast. Ask to be seated on the back deck if it&#39;s a nice day. It&#39;s covered and really pretty out there. So glad we didn&#39;t turn around and leave after the initial not-so-warm welcome.</p>

<p lang="en">One of my favorite things about living in this neighborhood. Yes, the line is always long for brunch. Does it go relatively fast despite the crowds outside? Yes. Is the wait worth it? Absolutely yes! Grab a coffee at Peet&#39;s, Wooden or Reverie Cafe while you wait, or wait for your name to be called next door at Finnegans Wake. The food is delicious and the drinks rival the food! Bloody Mary&#39;s and mimosas a plenty! No need to tip because they&#39;ve already factored the cost of &#34;living&#34; and health insurance in for their employees which is AMAZING. I wish more places did that!</p>

<span >

<p lang="en">This place was amazing.  Cute little French restaurant,. We sat out in covered patio. For starters we had assiste de formagio ; cheese with fig and walnuts. A must, one of the cheese melts like butter but all 3 cheeses  are delish, notably different.  For my main entree , I tried their duck , wow!, it was delicious; #somethingnew #onpoint . It was delicious. Hands down, this place is one of my favorites. I gotta go back &amp; try their entire menu, &amp; word is that they switch up menu. <br><br>I should give them 5 stars. Maybe after my second visit.</p>

<p lang="en">Small cute space. Good vibe and friendly workers. <br>The food is average. The flavor is there but I had a few burnt potatoes in my home fries, and they didn&#39;t actually toast my toast, while burning the edges of my friends toast. <br>I went mid morning on a Monday and was lucky to find a place to seat a group of 5. Most of the tables are set up for two. <br>The bathroom is extremely small and awkward, as the door does not close shut, it is just a barn style door and you can hear the workers talking right outside. <br>I ordered the Greece scramble and was pleased with the flavor as well as the amount of spinach onion and feta in the eggs. <br>It&#39;s a cute little place with good food, I would suggest it if you are near by looking for brunch but it doesn&#39;t hit the &#34;must have&#34; list for me.</p>

<div class="ywidget js-from-biz-owner">
<h3>From the business</h3>
<p>
Zazie has been rated &#34;Best Brunch in the Bay Area&#34; by multiple publications over the last 18 years, including the SF Chronicle, Bay Guardian, and SF Weekly. Michael Bauer last

</p>

<a class="link-more" href="javascript:;">
Learn more about Zazie
<span class="offscreen">, Opens a popup</span>
</a>

<div class="hidden from-biz-owner-wrapper">
<div class="from-biz-owner-content">
<h3>Specialties</h3>
<p>
Zazie has been rated &#34;Best Brunch in the Bay Area&#34; by multiple publications over the last 18 years, including the SF Chronicle, Bay Guardian, and SF Weekly. &nbsp;Michael Bauer last reviewed Zazie with the headline, &#34;Zazie brings brunch to new heights.&#34; &nbsp;We are famous for our specialty pancakes, including Gingerbread Pancakes with lemon curd and roasted bosc pears, Lemon-Ricotta pancakes, and Sugar Pie Pumpkin Spice Pancakes. &nbsp;Our benedict dishes are also exceptional, with the best hollandaise in town.<br><br>For dinner, we specialize in &nbsp;Southern French/ Californian cuisine, with slow braised dishes and fresh fish. &nbsp;Our wine list concentrates on small, family owned winemakers with less than 500 case productions. &nbsp;The menu changes seasonally; check online for updates.<br><br>Our heated garden patio is one of the few places in SF where you can comfortably dine outside under the stars, and inside the soaring ceilings and original 1876 brick wall make Zazie a unique SF treat.
</p>

<h3>History</h3>
<p>
Established in 1992.
</p>

<p>
Catherine Opoix opened Zazie as one of the first restaurants in what was to become the bustling restaurant scene of sleepy Cole Valley in 1992. &nbsp;Jennifer Piallat became general manager in 2000, then purchased the restaurant in 2005, bringing long time server Mario Rojas up to general manager. &nbsp;Since becoming the first non-union restaurant in SF to offer full benefits and a retirement plan, Zazie now retains an amazing staff who are knowledgable and eager to please.
</p>

</div>

</div>
